The '''A6003''' is an A-class road in [[England]], linking [[Kettering]] in [[Northamptonshire]] with [[Corby]] and [[Oakham]], the latter in [[Rutland]]. The road briefly enters [[Leicestershire]] between the villages of [[Rockingham, Northamptonshire|Rockingham]] and [[Caldecott, Rutland|Caldecott]]. The road forms the principal link between Corby and the rest of Northamptonshire, as well as between Rutland and Northamptonshire. The entire length of the road is {{convert|21|mi|km}}.

==Route==
The road starts at junction 10 of the [[A14 road (England)|A14]], heading past [[Wicksteed Park]] and into Kettering. Through the town it is a single carriageway until crossing the [[A43 road|A43]] at a [[Traffic light|signal-]][[Roundabout#Controlled_roundabouts|controlled roundabout]]. From here it passes an industrial development and heads north towards Corby. The stretch between the A43 and the [[A6014 road]] in Corby is the only length of [[dual carriageway]] on the route. As at July 2012 a [[Bypass route|bypass]] is under construction from Barford Bridge on the A6003 to the A43 west of [[Stanion]] to relieve the traffic on the single carriageway passing through [[Geddington]] on the A43.<ref>[http://assets.dft.gov.uk/publications/investment-in-local-major-transport-schemes-update/A43-Corby.pdf Department for transport A14 - A43 link road, accessed 18 September 2012] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121224055528/http://assets.dft.gov.uk/publications/investment-in-local-major-transport-schemes-update/A43-Corby.pdf |date=24 December 2012 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.theconstructionindex.co.uk/news/view/interserve-wins-24m-corby-link-road ''Interserve win £24m contract to build the new A43 Corby link road for Northamptonshire County Council'' Construction Index 25 June 2012 accessed 18 September 2012]</ref> Skirting the edge of Corby, the road passes the [[Eyebrook Reservoir]] before crossing the [[A47 road|A47]] at a roundabout at [[Uppingham]]. North of here it passes [[Rutland Water]] before arriving at [[Oakham]], where a new bypass has been constructed.

