{{About|a Thai national park|use of the name in Thai folklore|Rocket Festival}} {{Infobox Protected area | name = Pha Daeng National Park | alt_name =อุทยานแห่งชาติผาแดง | iucn_category = II | photo = ChiangDao_Waterfall.JPG | photo_caption = | map = Thailand | map_alt = | map_caption = Location within Thailand | map_width = | location = [[Chiang Dao District]], [[Chiang Mai Province]], [[Thailand]] | nearest_city = | coordinates = {{coord|19|37|43.025|N|98|57|21.772|E|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | area = 1,123 km<sup>2</sup> | established = 2 Nov 2000 | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | governing_body = }}
'''Pha Daeng National Park''' ({{lang-th|อุทยานแห่งชาติผาแดง}}), formerly known as '''Chiang Dao National Park''',<ref>{{cite web|title=Pha Daeng National Park|url=http://park.dnp.go.th/visitor/nationparkshow.php?PTA_CODE=1098|website=National Parks Thailand|publisher=Dept of National Parks Thailand|accessdate=2016-07-14|language=Thai}}</ref> is a [[List of national parks of Thailand|national park]] in [[Chiang Mai Province]], [[Thailand]]. Established on 2 November 2000, the park covers 1,123 km<sup>2</sup> of the [[Pha Daeng]] mountain areas of the [[Daen Lao Range]] near the border with [[Burma]], just north of [[Chiang Dao Wildlife Sanctuary]]. The tallest summit is 1,794 m high [[Doi Puk Phakka]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Pha Daeng National Park|url=http://www.dnp.go.th/parkreserve/asp/style1/default.asp?npid=167&lg=2|website=National Parks Thailand|publisher=Dept of National Parks Thailand|accessdate=2014-12-06|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141208192337/http://www.dnp.go.th/parkreserve/asp/style1/default.asp?npid=167&lg=2|archivedate=2014-12-08}}</ref>
